08934nam a22011295i 9783110266962DE-B159720221201113901.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||221201t20132013gw     fo  d z      eng d  a(OCoLC)851240258  a97831102669627 a10.1515/97831102669622doi  a(DE-B1597)173512  a(OCoLC)840047048  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 7aREL0810002bisacsh00aRabbi - Pastor - Priest :bTheir Roles and Profiles Through the Ages /ced. by Walter Homolka, Heinz-Günther Schöttler. 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter, c[2013] 4c©2013  a1 online resource (377 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aStudia Judaica : Forschungen zur Wissenschaft des Judentums ,x0585-5306 ;v6400tFrontmatter -- tInhalt -- tPreface -- tThe Talmudic Rabbi as Holy Man -- tOffices? Roles, Functions, Authorities and Their Ethos in Earliest Christianity: A Look into the World of Pauline Communities -- tInsights into the Christian Office in Late Antiquity -- tMen of Knowledge and Power: A Tentative Profile of Medieval Rabbis -- tChange or Continuity? How the Reformation Changed the Role of the Pastor -- tModern Rabbinical Training: Intercultural Invention and Political Reconfiguration -- tRabbis as Preachers, 1800–1965: Regensburg Conference Lecture -- tThe Professionalization of the American Rabbinate -- tThe Protestant Pastoral Office: Its Self-Understanding and Its Challenges Today -- tWhom Does the Priest Represent? The Theology of the Ordained Ministry Following the Second Vatican Council (1962–1965) -- tThe Protestant Pastor and the Communication of the Gospel: Public Ministry in the Present Protestant Church -- tA Female Rabbi Is Like an Orange on the Passover Plate. Women and the Rabbinate: Challenges and Horizons -- tFunctional Secularization and Conversion: On the Changed Demands Made on Ministerial Action in the Catholic Church -- tIslamic Clerics: Tradition and Transition -- t“… Invited to Preach to the People” (Origen): A Theological Plea for “Lay” Preaching in the Catholic Church -- tWord Workers: The Rabbinate and the Protestant Pastoral Office in Dialogue -- tThe Modern Community Rabbi in Germany: Towards the Development of a Contemporary Occupational Profile -- tList of Contributors -- tIndex of Abbreviations -- tIndex of Names -- tIndex of Subjects0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aBoth Judaism and Christianity have authorized clergy, charged with fulfilling a multitude of tasks in their respective communities. They teach, provide pastoral care, and preach. They lead worship, hold services and offer counseling regarding all aspects of life. They perform religious rites at the beginning and end of life as well as in-between. They make decisions regarding religious questions, serve as administrators, and possibly even mediate ‛between heaven and earth’. The concrete forms of realization and the functions of the office are not only defined through theological specification but are also subject to trends and influences. This in turn leads to constant change and adaptation.  aJudentum und Christentum haben ihre offiziell beauftragten Amtsträger, um die vielfältigen Aufgaben der Gemeinschaft zu erfüllen: zu sammeln und zu lehren, seelsorglich tätig zu sein und zu predigen, Gottesdienste zu leiten und Lebenshilfe zu geben, Rituale zu vollziehen am Beginn des Lebens, an dessen Ende und mitten im Leben, in religiösen Fragen zu entscheiden, administrativ tätig zu werden und vielleicht sogar ‛zwischen Himmel und Erde’ zu vermitteln.Die konkreten Verwirklichungsformen und Funktionen des Amtes (und der Amtsträger) sind dabei einem ständigen Wandel unterworfen. Mit diesem Funktionswandel reagieren Religionsgemeinschaften auf die sich verändernden Bedingungen des Glaubens und der religiösen Praxis. Die Beiträge gehen diesen Erwartungen an geistliche Amtsträger, an ihre Identität und Legitimation im Wandel der letzten Jahrhunderte nach und bringen diese auf zwei Ebenen zur Sprache: auf der Ebene der Leitbilder und auf der Ebene der realen Erscheinungsformen, die die jeweiligen geschichtlichen, kulturellen und sozialen Gegebenheiten hervorgebracht haben.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aGeistliches Amt. 4aPastor. 4aPastoraltheologie. 4aPriester. 4aRabbiner. 7aRELIGION / Clergy.2bisacsh  aPastor.  aPastoral Theology.  aPriest.  aRabbi.  aSpiritual Ministry.1 aBonfil, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDeeg, Alexander, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDirscherl, Erwin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFirestone, Reuven, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFörst, Johannes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHauptman, Judith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHerms, Eilert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoffman, Lawrence A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHomolka, Walter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHomolka, Walter, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKampmann, Jürgen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarx, Dalia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNicklas, Tobias, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSaperstein, Marc, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchöttler, Heinz-Günther, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchöttler, Heinz-Günther, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vo